</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/uarisensun.showPublicProfile?language=EN>arisensun</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Regular Poster</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(11/21/01 10:26:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=599.topic&index=30>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dear Santa</span><hr size=1> My opinion is that you shy away from the larger computer companies.  I would go with a smaller computer company that can provide several references about how great there computers are.  I always' build my own computer systems, this is what I use..  <br>
<br>
Processor: AMD or P4 -- AMD is cheaper, but less stable.  With any AMD system I recommend extra cooling.  <br>
<br>
Motherboard: Iwill or Asus -- Iwill is cheaper, less features.  Asus is pretty damn amazing.<br>
<br>
Ram: Micron -- Best ram available. $44 for a 256 mb stick<br>
<br>
Video Card: Geforce 2 or 3 -- Depending on what you spend on your card.<br>
<br>
Sound Card: Creative always, either a SB live or Ensonique.<br>
<br>
CD Burner: TDK.  They are making the best burner out right now,  It cost's around $135 at cosco.  Smartburn technology is amazing.<br>
<br>
CD Rom: Doesn't matter much.<br>
<br>
Floppy Drive: Doesn't Matter much.<br>
<br>
Case: Antek is very very nice!  Not a bad price either.<br>
<br>
<br>
